race.comment: LITTLE SILVER (4) was only caught late last start over the mile here 21 days ago and coming back to this distance looks a good move. He maps to get every chance under Faithfull and the form from his last start effort has worked out well. Back to an easier race today and looks poised to strike. SIXINCH HEELS (14) is on the quick turnaround today and steps up to 1400m where she's been successful previously. Needs some luck from the barrier, but she's building nicely in recent runs and can play a leading role. CORRECT CHOICE (7) just missed first-up behind Essentric Nature and that form may have been given a push earlier today. The wide draw is a niggle, but he can build on the fresh effort and put his best foot forward. SATURDAY SESH (11) is better than he showed last time out and can make his presence felt. ANGEL UNDERCOVER (1) drops right back in grade today third-up and can be in the finish.
